-- 27-self-optimizing-cell-frames.cell — full eval-one execution trace
--
-- Self-Optimizing Cell: takes p2-spawner-cascade.cell from R15, analyzes
-- for redundancies, optimizes, re-executes, compares. ⊢∘ loop ensures
-- semantics preservation.
--
-- Ready set analysis (initial):
--   source-program: ⊢= with no given → READY
--   analyze-redundancy: given §source-program→§program, source-program→program-text → BLOCKED
--   propose-optimization: given analyze-redundancy→* → BLOCKED
--   execute-original: given source-program→program-text → BLOCKED (but will unblock with source-program)
--   execute-optimized: given propose-optimization→optimized-text → BLOCKED
--   compare: given execute-original→*, execute-optimized→* → BLOCKED
--   ⊢∘ optimize: coordinates iteration → BLOCKED (manages loop)
--   report: given all compare→* and propose-optimization→* → BLOCKED

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- FRAME 0: evaluate source-program (⊢= trivial pass-through)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Ready set: { source-program }
-- All other cells blocked on source-program→*

⊢ source-program
  yield §program, program-text

  yield §program ≡ §p2-spawner-cascade
  yield program-text ≡ "
    ⊢ topic
      given subject ≡ \"Why do cats purr?\"
      yield subject, depth
      ⊢= depth ← 1
      ⊨ depth = 1

    ⊢⊢ decompose
      given topic→subject
      given topic→depth
      yield sub-questions[]
      until length(sub-questions) ≥ 3
      max 5
      ∴ Break «topic→subject» into 3 independent sub-questions.
        Each sub-question should be answerable on its own.
        Each sub-question should cover a different aspect.
      ⊨ length(sub-questions) ≥ 3
      ⊨ each sub-question is a complete question

    ⊢ synthesize
      given decompose→sub-questions
      given answer-*→response
      yield summary
      ∴ Given these sub-answers about «topic→subject»:
        «answer-*→response»
        Synthesize into a single coherent 3-sentence explanation.
      ⊨ summary is 3 sentences
      ⊨ summary addresses the original question
      ⊨? on failure:
        retry with \"Be more concise — exactly 3 sentences\" appended
        max 2
      ⊨? on exhaustion:
        partial-accept(best)
  "

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ program-text contains at least 3 cell declarations → ✓
--     (topic, decompose, synthesize — 3 declarations found)
--   ⊨ §program is a valid Cell program → ✓
--     (all symbols valid: ⊢, ⊢⊢, ⊢=, ⊨, ⊨?, ∴, «», →)

-- state after frame 0: source-program frozen.
-- Ready set: { analyze-redundancy, execute-original }
--   analyze-redundancy: needs §source-program→§program ✓, source-program→program-text ✓ → READY
--   execute-original: needs source-program→program-text ✓ → READY
-- Confluence: either can go first. Picking analyze-redundancy (primary path).

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- FRAME 1: evaluate analyze-redundancy (soft cell, LLM)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Ready set: { analyze-redundancy, execute-original }
-- Picking analyze-redundancy (drives optimization path)

⊢ analyze-redundancy
  given §source-program→§program ≡ §p2-spawner-cascade
  given source-program→program-text ≡ "..." -- (full text as above)
  yield redundancies[], tautologies[], unnecessary-deps[], analysis

  ∴ Read the program carefully. Identify redundancies...

-- LLM evaluation (simulated):

  yield tautologies ≡ [
    "T1: topic declares ⊢= depth ← 1 then ⊨ depth = 1. The oracle just restates the deterministic binding. It can never fail — the value IS 1 by definition. This is a tautological oracle."
  ]

  yield redundancies ≡ [
    "R1: topic→depth is consumed by decompose as a given, but decompose→∴ body never references «topic→depth» — it only uses «topic→subject». The depth yield exists in topic but serves no purpose in the current program. The depth field and its oracle are dead code.",
    "R2: decompose has oracle ⊨ length(sub-questions) ≥ 3 AND until clause length(sub-questions) ≥ 3. The until clause already enforces the same condition as a termination guard. The oracle is redundant with the spawner's own until — if until is satisfied, the oracle trivially passes."
  ]

  yield unnecessary-deps ≡ [
    "D1: decompose declares 'given topic→depth' but the ∴ body only references «topic→subject». The depth dependency creates a false scheduling constraint — decompose cannot run until depth is bound, but it never uses the value."
  ]

  yield analysis ≡ "The p2-spawner-cascade program has 3 optimizable findings:

    TAUTOLOGY T1: In cell 'topic', the oracle ⊨ depth = 1 is tautological because ⊢= depth ← 1 deterministically binds depth to 1. The oracle can never fail. Safe to remove — the ⊢= binding is its own proof.

    REDUNDANCY R1: topic yields 'depth' which is consumed by decompose, but decompose's ∴ body never interpolates «topic→depth». The entire depth pipeline (yield depth in topic, given topic→depth in decompose) is dead code. Safe to remove — no downstream cell uses the value.

    REDUNDANCY R2: decompose has ⊨ length(sub-questions) ≥ 3 which duplicates the until clause. The until clause is structural (controls spawner termination). The oracle re-checks the same property. One is sufficient. The until clause is more important (it controls execution), so the oracle is the redundant one.

    UNNECESSARY DEP D1: decompose declares given topic→depth but never uses it. This forces decompose to wait for depth to be bound, adding a false scheduling dependency. In this small program depth is bound instantly (same cell), so the latency impact is zero — but it's still a semantic falsehood in the dependency graph. Safe to remove."

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ analysis explains each finding with specific references to cells → ✓
--     (references topic, decompose, specific oracles and deps)
--   ⊨ each redundancy has a proposed removal that preserves semantics → ✓
--     (T1: remove oracle, R1: remove depth pipeline, R2: remove redundant oracle, D1: remove given)

-- state after frame 1: analyze-redundancy frozen.
