  yield original-output ≡ "Cats purr through rapid laryngeal muscle contractions that vibrate the vocal cords at 25-150 Hz during breathing. They purr in both positive contexts like contentment and negative ones like stress or injury, serving social and self-soothing purposes. The vibration frequencies also promote bone density and tissue healing, suggesting purring evolved as a low-energy biological repair mechanism."

  yield original-steps ≡ 6

