-- Total eval-one frames: 7 (frames 0-6)
-- ⊢∘ optimize iterations: 1 (converged immediately)
-- Cells evaluated: source-program, analyze-redundancy, execute-original,
--   propose-optimization, execute-optimized, compare, report
-- Oracle checks: 14 total (2 + 2 + 2 + 3 + 2 + 2 + 2), 1 tautological removed
--
-- Findings:
--   - 1 tautological oracle removed (T1: depth = 1)
--   - 2 redundancies removed (R1: dead depth pipeline, R2: oracle duplicating until)
--   - 1 unnecessary dependency removed (D1: unused topic→depth in decompose)
--   - Net reduction: 7 lines, 0 step reduction, cleaner dependency graph
--
-- Key insight: tautological oracles on ⊢= bindings are the most common
-- waste pattern — the deterministic binding IS the proof. Oracles add
-- value only when they check properties NOT implied by the cell's own
-- definition.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- OBSERVATIONS
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

⊢= obs-tautology-pattern
  ∴ When ⊢= x ← v is followed by ⊨ x = v, the oracle is tautological.
    Deterministic bindings are self-proving. Oracles should check properties
    that emerge from computation, not restate the computation itself.

⊢= obs-until-oracle-redundancy
  ∴ Spawner until clauses and ⊨ assertions on the same property are redundant.
    The until is structural (controls termination). The oracle re-verifies
    what the runtime already enforced. Keep the until, drop the oracle.

⊢= obs-dead-dep-detection
  ∴ A dependency is dead when the cell's ∴ body never interpolates the
    referenced value with «». Static analysis: scan ∴ for guillemet
    references, compare to given declarations. Mismatch = dead dependency.
    This is crystallizable — a ⊢= cell could perform this check.

⊢= obs-optimization-convergence
  ∴ The ⊢∘ loop converged in 1 iteration because all optimizations were
    conservative (removing dead code and tautologies). More aggressive
    optimizations (cell merging, ∴ rewriting) would likely require multiple
    iterations as they risk changing semantics. Conservative-first is the
    right strategy for self-optimization.

⊢= obs-step-vs-overhead
  ∴ Eval-one step count measures cell evaluations. Oracle check count
    measures verification overhead. This optimization reduced oracle checks
    (fewer oracles to evaluate) without reducing steps (same cells to run).
    Both metrics matter: steps measure latency, oracle checks measure cost.
